Title: Non-Abelian Constraints in Multiparticle Production
Authors: Ludwik Turko
Comments: Talk given at the Cracow Epiphany Conference on Quarks and Gluons in
  Extreme Conditions, Cracow, Poland, January 3-6, 2002. To be published in
  Acta Physica Polonica B. 9 pages, 1 figure
Journal-ref: Acta Phys.Polon. B33 (2002) 1533-1542
\\
  Internal microscopic symmetry of a many body system leads to global
constraints. We obtain explicit forms of the global macroscopic condition
assuring that at the microscopic level the evolution respects the overall
symmetry.
